---
/**
 * streaming-event-driven · exactly-once-kafka-deep-dive · Figure 1 — the EOS pipeline hero.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/streaming-event-driven/exactly-once-kafka-deep-dive.html (figure + svg +
 * figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the MDX, because
 * MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case
 * attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, marker-end, …). In an .astro
 * file the SVG is plain HTML, so it renders byte-for-byte. The marker refs
 * (#arw, #arwA, #arwG) point at the shared arrowhead <defs> emitted once in the
 * MDX body, exactly as in the source DOM.
 */
---

<figure style="margin-top:1.6rem">
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 240"
        role="img"
        aria-label="The exactly-once pipeline: consume from an input topic, process, produce to an output topic, with the input offset committed inside the same transaction, read by a read_committed consumer"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="24"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">THE EXACTLY-ONCE LOOP — Kafka in, process, Kafka out</text
            >
            <!-- input topic -->
            <rect x="10" y="58" width="96" height="48" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
            <text x="58" y="80" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >Input topic</text
            >
            <text x="58" y="96" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f">consume</text>
            <!-- processor / producer -->
            <rect
                x="146"
                y="50"
                width="160"
                height="64"
                rx="10"
                fill="#f1eee2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="226"
                y="74"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">read-process-write</text
            >
            <text x="226" y="92" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >txnal producer + consumer</text
            >
            <text x="226" y="105" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >transactional.id (stable)</text
            >
            <!-- output topic -->
            <rect x="346" y="58" width="96" height="48" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
            <text
                x="394"
                y="80"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">Output topic</text
            >
            <text x="394" y="96" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f">produce</text>
            <!-- downstream consumer -->
            <rect x="494" y="58" width="136" height="48" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text
                x="562"
                y="78"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">Downstream</text
            >
            <text x="562" y="94" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >read_committed</text
            >
            <!-- forward arrows -->
            <line x1="108" y1="82" x2="144" y2="82" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line x1="308" y1="82" x2="344" y2="82" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
            <line x1="444" y1="82" x2="492" y2="82" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <!-- the trick: offset committed inside transaction -->
            <rect
                x="120"
                y="150"
                width="320"
                height="40"
                rx="8"
                fill="#fbfaf2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-dasharray="4 3"></rect>
            <text
                x="280"
                y="167"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">ONE transaction wraps: output records + input-offset commit</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="182" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >commit → both visible · abort/crash → neither happens</text
            >
            <path d="M 226 114 L 250 148" fill="none" stroke="#7a1f12" marker-end="url(#arwA)"
            ></path>
            <path
                d="M 394 108 C 410 130, 400 140, 380 150"
                fill="none"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-dasharray="3 2"
                marker-end="url(#arwA)"></path>
            <text x="320" y="222" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#9a2417"
                >↑ leave Kafka here (DB · card · email) and EOS no longer applies</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Memorise this banner. Every level below explains one box, one arrow, or the dashed
        transaction that binds output to input-offset.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
